id: pm-gsoe
title: "pm telemetry stats: add error_rate and resolution breakdown per command bucket"
description: pm telemetry stats buckets commands by count and event_type_counts (command_start / command_finish) but does not surface success/failure rates or command_resolution distribution within the local queue. This makes it impossible to detect a degraded-error-rate locally without querying the remote stack. command_finish events already carry ok (bool) and command_resolution fields.
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[2]: "area:observability","area:telemetry"
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:04:45.137Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-18T14:34:46.678Z"
author: audit-observability-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Each bucket gains: ok_count, error_count (derived from command_finish ok field); error_rate (0–1 float, absent when no finish events); command_resolution_counts (map of resolution -> count).\n- ok_count + error_count == number of command_finish events in that bucket.\n- pm telemetry stats output includes these fields.\n- Unit tests assert correct tallying and that missing/malformed payload.ok is treated as not-ok (conservative)."
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: pm telemetry stats now reports ok_count/error_count/error_rate and command_resolution_counts per command bucket from command_finish payloads; missing/non-true ok counted conservatively as error.
expected_result: Each bucket reports ok_count/error_count/error_rate and command_resolution_counts from command_finish payloads.
actual_result: Conservative ok handling and resolution tally verified; ok_count+error_count==finish count; 100/100/100/100.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-18T14:34:26.517Z",claude-code-agent,"Bundled with pm-3n3b/pm-fbyu in one PR (epic pm-5oj5). ok_count/error_count/error_rate (conservative: missing/non-true ok counts as error) + command_resolution_counts derived from command_finish payloads. ok_count+error_count == finish-event count by construction. Coverage 100/100/100/100."
files[2]{path,scope,note}:
  src/cli/commands/telemetry.ts,project,ok_count/error_count/error_rate/command_resolution_counts
  tests/unit/commands/telemetry-command.spec.ts,project,conservative ok + resolution tally coverage
close_reason: Shipped local error-rate + resolution breakdown in telemetry stats with full unit coverage; 100/100/100/100.
body: "## Context\n\nFile: src/cli/commands/telemetry.ts:199-253 — buildTelemetryStatsBuckets. Currently tracks count, max_attempts, event_type_counts, schema versions. Fields ok and command_resolution from command_finish payload (runtime.ts:927-930) are not extracted.\n\nFile: src/core/telemetry/runtime.ts:927 — command_resolution emitted in command_finish payload at all capture levels.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- Each bucket gains: ok_count, error_count (derived from command_finish ok field); error_rate (0–1 float, absent when no finish events); command_resolution_counts (map of resolution -> count).\n- ok_count + error_count == number of command_finish events in that bucket.\n- pm telemetry stats output includes these fields.\n- Unit tests assert correct tallying and that missing/malformed payload.ok is treated as not-ok (conservative).\n\n## Evidence\n\nsrc/cli/commands/telemetry.ts:211 — eventType is parsed; payload fields are not.\nsrc/core/telemetry/runtime.ts:927 — command_resolution present in finish payload at all capture levels."
